name: .EMBR File Extension
summary: Learn about .EMBR files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: GIS file format developed by GEOREID Pty Ltd, a company that specializes in GIS data collection, site surveying, and analysis; used to store statistical geodatabase data such as calculated lengths or volumes at a set point in time; contains information in plain text.

content: The EMBR file allows you to organize calculated information for various purposes such as calculating projections and comparing data. The information is stored in a format that doesn't require any special software to view the contents. You can open the EMBR file with text editors such as Notepad and WordPad. Also, you can use the ArcGIS program to update the information in an EMBR file.
